    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small triangular flags in paper or fabric, illustrated with a saint, the church or chapel where the saint is venerated, and occasionally scenes from the life of the saint, or events occurring at the church or chapel. These were typically sold as souvenirs of the pilgrimage itself.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
